{"author":{"id":"977fec8a59c245f25e0e700fa290ef50836c624572869487e9e47fedc85061ee"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1445083362,"nonce":"6uZPKV+lMtBY9jMjo5bCoiWbQkE=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDE0ODkxMjQwOA==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/332#issuecomment-148912408"},"message":"\u003e Different number of columns, different headers/comment lines. Thinking about it I don't know what is similar between them ;)\n\nIsn't that what metadata is good for?\n\n\u003e featureCount is even worse, as it does not mark the comment line with # or similar symbols. \n\u003e So we need to recognise Geneid 1:, which is not really unique. Also please consider what happens if this identifier is changing between featureCounts versions, for example to Gene-ID 1:. You need to have a new data type to detect this. Versioned datatypes are currently not supported.\n\nWell, if this happens, the featureCounts wrapper should introduce a new datatype (like GFF and GFF3 are not exactly the same ... yet on a certain level interoperable). I'm seeing this from the angle of the tool wrapper \"explaining\" what kind of data it is producing. If tools can register new datatypes, I don't see the harm of having a few hundred different datatypes.","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1445083978,"nonce":"RwZPB49qZdS6kQTYwmAK13vhGsk=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDE0ODkxMjgyMA==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/332#issuecomment-148912820"},"message":"Well it's a complex issue, and I am not even sure what we can do with the current state of the system, so I should better get informed :).","files":null}]}